caption:
Chobani celebrates good food for all. And we’re celebrating #BHM with just that: good food from the Black community.
@shaneebenjamin’s bowl of gumbo—a Louisiana Creole staple that should not be confused with Cajun gumbo—looks good enough to eat on a purple, green, and gold tablecloth: the festive tricolor pattern ubiquitous to Mardi Gras in New Orleans. More on the way from @shaneebenjamin coming this month
